Acquiring the package:

      There are two versions of ACCOUNT available.  You will only need to
      obtain one of them:
 
      1.  The file "a05acc.bas" is the original uncompressed Basic source
          code, and as such should be fairly readable.  This can be obtained
          and *EXEC-ed as normal.  However it will not run on a standard
          Model B because of lack of memory.
 
      2.  The file "a05acc.hex" is the same program, but compressed and then
          'hexified'.  Transfer the file and use the Lancaster 'dehexing'
          program.  This will produce a file containing a 'SAVE-d' Basic
          program (LOAD and RUN it, don't *EXEC it!).  This will run on a
          standard Model B.
 
